      "watchedDate": "2026-06-06",
      "review": "In solitude, I felt the liberty you spoke of. \n\nBut I also felt your absence.Genuinely the most attached I have felt to romance film in a while. Similar vibes to (500) Days of Summer and Atonement. But what I especially loved was how art and fire was a representation of the fleeting nature and impermanence of love. Not a cliché, but an unparalleled expression of love through silence. \n\nPotential parallels to Dorian Gray, not sure... Left in tears. Someone else described this as that feeling of staring at a crackling fire, and that is beyond accurate. Those last 15 minutes had me sniffling and I am half convinced I was the only one. Rose instantly to the top four and might stay there. My appreciation for art triumphs any dopamine-seeking movie.at one point, we stop"
